description: Deletes up to ten messages from the specified queue. This is a batch version of DeleteMessage. The result of the action on each message is reported individually in the response.

parameters.name: QueueUrl
parameters.description: The URL of the Amazon SQS queue from which messages are deleted. Queue URLs and names are case-sensitive.

parameters.name: Entries
parameters.description: Lists the receipt handles for the messages to be deleted. (dict) --- Encloses a receipt handle and an identifier for it. The identifier for this particular receipt handle. This is used to communicate the result. A receipt handle.

nested_params.name: Id
nested_params.description: The identifier for this particular receipt handle. This is used to communicate the result.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The Id of an entry in a batch request.

nested_items.name: SenderFault
nested_items.description: Specifies whether the error happened due to the caller of the batch API action.

nested_items.name: Code
nested_items.description: An error code representing why the action failed on this entry.

nested_items.name: Message
nested_items.description: A message explaining why the action failed on this entry.
